15500.name: Sel Mahum Diary
15500.description: Diary containing the daily life of the Sel Mahum. Take it back to Guard Stan of Oren Village.

15501.name: Sel Mahum Cookbook Page
15501.description: Part of the cookbook used by the Sel Mahum Chef. Take it back to Guard Stan of Oren Village.

15502.name: Sel Mahum Cookbook
15502.description: Cookbook used by the Sel Mahum Chef. Take it back to Guard Stan of Oren Village.

15503.name: Shiny Salmon
15503.description: Shiny and tantalizing salmon. Take it back to Guard Stan of Oren Village.

15504.name: Gray Salmon
15504.description: Not so shiny but still OK-looking salmon. If you take it back to Guard Stan of Oren Village, he'll take care of everything else, right?

15505.name: Sickly Salmon
15505.description: Scales are falling off and it doesn't look good at all. If you take it back to Guard Stan of Oren Village, he'll take care of everything else, right?

15506.name: Salmon Lure
15506.description: Lure used to catch salmon. You cannot catch salmon without it.

15507.name: Foul Fruit
15507.description: Horrible tasting fruit. If you put it in the salmon porridge, which is cooking on the fire at the Sel Mahum Training Grounds, you could ruin the dish. Awful Soup

15508.name: Sel Mahum Training Diary
15508.description: Dairy containing detailed examples of the Sel Mahum training. Take it back to Guard Pinaps of Oren Village.

15509.name: Sel Mahum Training Timetable
15509.description: Paper containing the training schedule of the Sel Mahum. Take it back to Guard Pinaps of Oren Village.

15510.name: Golem Corps Log
15510.description: Paper containing some logs for recognizing Golem Corps. Collect all needed logs.

15511.name: Golem Corps Collection
15511.description: Bundle of papers containing all the logs for recognizing Golem Corps. Take it back to Collector Gutenhagen at Pavel Ruins.

15512.name: Seed of Annihilation Orders
15512.description: Kucereus' Clan Outpost Commander Kbaldir's written orders. Go to the pier of the Seed of Annihilation and deliver it to his subordinate, Officer Klemis.

15513.name: Gracian Soldier Tag
15513.description: ID Tag of a Gracian soldier who was killed near the Seed of Annihilation. Let's take it to Officer Jakan who is stationed at the pier near the Seed of Annihilation.

15514.name: Cold Resistance Potion
15514.description: A potion especially crafted from the Jinia Guild to protect the body from the cursed cold powers of the Ice Queen. Needed to rescue Kegor, who has fallen into trouble.

15515.name: Seal Breaker - 5th Floor
15515.description: Seal Breaker needed to speak face to face with the Demon Prince on the 5th floor of the Tower of Infinitum in the Steel Citadel. It is destroyed after one use.

15516.name: Seal Breaker - 10th Floor
15516.description: Seal Breaker needed to speak face to face with Ranku on the 10th floor of the Tower of Infinitum in the Steel Citadel. It is destroyed after one use.

15517.name: Seal Components Part 1
15517.description: A Seal Breaker component. Acquired after defeating the Space Guard in the Tower of Infinitum. You can make a Seal Breaker that negates great power by putting this piece together with others like it.

15518.name: Seal Components Part 2
15518.description: A Seal Breaker component. Acquired after defeating the Space Gazer in the Tower of Infinitum. You can make a Seal Breaker that negates great power by putting this piece together with others like it.

15519.name: Seal Components Part 3
15519.description: A Seal Breaker component. Acquired after defeating the Space Priest in the Tower of Infinitum. You can make a Seal Breaker that negates great power by putting this piece together with others like it.

15520.name: Seal Components Part 4
15520.description: A Seal Breaker component. Acquired after defeating the Space Ruler in the Tower of Infinitum. You can make a Seal Breaker that negates great power by putting this piece together with others like it.

15522.name: Shabby Necklace
15522.description: Shabby necklace that Watcher of Antharas Theodric supposedly gives only to those who are worthy of going after the Earth Dragon Antharas. He says the necklace will transform after you defeat Antharas.

15523.name: Miracle Necklace
15523.description: After you defeated the Earth dragon Antharas, the shabby necklace that you received from Watcher of Antharas Theodric changed into this item. Take this necklace to him.

15524.name: Poor Necklace
15524.description: Watcher of Valakas Klein gave you this necklace. It is of poor quality and not worth much. However, it is said to transform into something worth much more after killing Valakas.

15525.name: Valor Necklace
15525.description: After killing Valakas the Poor Necklace has transformed into this necklace. Take this necklace to Watcher of Valakas Klein.

15526.name: Tattered Monk Clothes
15526.description: Tattered clothes are the remains of the monks you battled in the Monastery of Silence. The clothes are nothing more than rags after their years of use. Let's take them to Greymore in the Monastery of Silence.

15527.name: Mark of Splendor
15527.description: Proof that you successfully defeated the Master of Splendor Anays at Priest Greymore's request. If you take it to Greymore, you will receive a reward.

15528.name: Mark of Darkness
15528.description: You succeeded in defeating the Master of Splendor Anays at Priest Greymore's request. But you received the Mark of Darkness rather than the Mark of Splendor. If you take this to Greymore, he will laugh at you.

15529.name: Priest Dominic's Letter
15529.description: A secret letter sent by Priest Dominic of the Rune Village temple to Greymore. Deliver it to Priest Greymore in the Monastery of Silence.

15530.name: Monk Scripture
15530.description: Sacred text obtained after defeating the monks in the Monastery of Silence. Bring it to Greymore in the Monastery of Silence.

15531.name: Sel Mahum Mane
15531.description: Mane obtained by defeating the Sel Mahums that were attacking the animals the Beast Farm. Collect them and bring them to Tunatun in the Beast Farm.

15532.name: Veal
15532.description: Meat from a young animal. Smells good but tastes bad. Take it to Beast Herder Tunatun at the Beast Farm.

15533.name: Innocence Jewel
15533.description: A white gem produce by animals. Looking at it reminds you of a time long ago. I wonder what my old friends are doing now

15534.name: Prime Meat
15534.description: Top quality meat obtained from an adult animal. Only one piece comes out per animal. Collect these and take them to Beast Herder Tunatun.

15535.name: Concentrated Spirit Energy
15535.description: Obtained in the Seed of Annihilation. Take this Concentrated Spirit Energy to Special Products Broker Kirklan to exchange them for a reward.

15536.name: Spirit Stone Dust
15536.description: Obtained through hunting in the Seed of Annihilation. If you take them to Special Products Broker Kirklan you can exchange 5 of these items for a Spirit Stone Fragment.

15537.name: Strongbox of Promise
15537.description: Small safe obtained by defeating the monks in the Monastery of Silence. You can find out about the quest by clicking on it. Quest start item.

15538.name: Book of Silence
15538.description: Ancient book contained inside the Strongbox of Promise. Before you can return it to its owner, you must figure out who it belongs to. Go to Library of Sages Director Sophia in the Rune Castle Library and ask for help.

15539.name: Book of Silence
15539.description: You heard about the book's owner from the Library of Sages Director Sophia. Return the book to its owner.

15540.name: Unlit Torchlight
15540.description: Torch that doesn't light. Item needed to obtain the treasure chest in the secret room inside the Monastery of Silence.

15541.name: Red Soul Crystal - Stage 17
15541.description: Red Crystal that absorbs souls, stage 17. Special abilities can be applied to the weapon when absorbing certain amount of souls. MP 26 is consumed each time of use. This level crystal is said to absorb crystals on its own, so it doesn't seem like you need to use it directly on the monsters. Soul Crystal

15542.name: Blue Soul Crystal - Stage 17
15542.description: Blue Crystal that absorbs souls, stage 17. Special abilities can be applied to the weapon when absorbing certain amount of souls. MP 26 is consumed each time of use. This level crystal is said to absorb crystals on its own, so it doesn't seem like you need to use it directly on the monsters. Soul Crystal

15543.name: Green Soul Crystal - Stage 17
15543.description: Green Crystal that absorbs souls, stage 17. Special abilities can be applied to the weapon when absorbing certain amount of souls. MP 26 is consumed each time of use. This level crystal is said to absorb crystals on its own, so it doesn't seem like you need to use it directly on the monsters. Soul Crystal
